<org.eclipse.epf.uma:ContentDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmi:id="-3hIx_RXsn-awuuChFvFCzw" name="meas_planning_elements,_cjtRgPhdEd2eD9_rTy05yw" guid="-3hIx_RXsn-awuuChFvFCzw" changeDate="2009-03-24T09:31:45.531-0700" version="7.5.0">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The contributing components should include all activities and tasks that directly contribute to defining, developing,&#xD;
    and implementing a Performance Measurement practice within an organization.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    These components should include plans and activities for engaging stakeholders in establishing and advancing the&#xD;
    solution framework envisioned for the performance measurement scope being addressed. Ideally, a business value workshop&#xD;
    should be incorporated into the project plan to facilitate identification of business drivers that affect IT delivery,&#xD;
    delivery problems that stakeholders are facing, and changes needed to more effectively address business needs.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The contributing components will also include tasks identified that are required to define business and operational&#xD;
    measures, define practice measures, detail measures, develop the associated measurement infrastructure, deploy the&#xD;
    measurement system, and assess the measurement system.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Inputs&lt;/strong> - tasks from:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Setting up a Performance Measurement System practice: &#xD;
        &lt;ul>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Define Business and Operational Measures&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Define Practice Measures&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Detail Measures&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Develop Measurement Infrastructure&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;/ul>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Managing Performance through Measurements practice: &#xD;
        &lt;ul>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Assess the Measurement System&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Deploy the Measurement System&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Manage the Measurement System&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;/ul>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Work Products&lt;/strong> - execution of the performance measurement related activities and tasks will result in&#xD;
    the following work products:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Measurement Infrastructure&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Measurement Requirements&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Measurement Specification&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Measurement&amp;nbsp;Process and Procedures&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Measurement Assessment&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></mainDescription>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:ContentDescription>
